[h1]Station Production Overview[/h1]

Adds a [b]Production Overview[/b] tab to the info panel tab strip in the map menu (alongside Object Info, Crew, etc.) for player-owned stations. Shows per-ware production and consumption rates, groups wares into Products, Intermediates, and Resources, and previews the impact of planned (not yet built) modules.

[h2][b]Features[/b][/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Production Overview Tab[/b]: Dedicated tab in the station info panel showing per-ware produced, consumed, and net total rates per hour.
[*] [b]Sector Production Overview[/b]: Same tab in the sector info panel, listing all player-owned production stations in the sector.
[*] [b]Ware grouping[/b]: Wares split into [b]Products[/b], [b]Intermediates[/b], and [b]Resources[/b]; workforce-only consumer goods placed in Resources unless also produced on-site.
[*] [b]Live vs Estimated mode[/b]: Dropdown switches between actual running rates (with [b]active/total[/b] module count) and theoretical maximum output.
[*] [b]Production issue indicators[/b]: Wares with modules waiting on resources or storage are highlighted, with a tooltip showing exact issue counts.
[*] [b]Planned module preview[/b]: A delta row per ware shows the production impact of unbuilt modules in the construction plan.
[*] [b]Empire balance[/b]: Optional [i]All stations:[/i] sub-row (toggle via [b]Show empire balance[/b] checkbox, single-station view only) shows empire-wide production, consumption, and coloured surplus/deficit for each Product and Intermediate.
[*] [b]Configurable data refresh[/b]: Slider in [b]Extension options > Station Production Overview[/b] sets the cache duration in UI ticks (1-10, default 3).
[*] [b]Quick-navigation buttons[/b]: [i]Configure Station[/i] and [i]Station Overview[/i] at the bottom of the tab.
[/list]
